						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vikramachōḻa. Year 3: A.D. 1121.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems that a group of <hi rend="italic">[śiva-brāhmaṇas]</hi> of the temple of Tirumayāṉa[m Uḍaiyār] in Nālūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vāṉavanmādēvichchaturvēdimaṅgalam in Chēṟṟūr-kūṟṟam, a subdivision of [Kulōttuṅga] chōḻavaḷanāḍu accepted money and agreed to maintain one perpetual lamp in the temple.</p>						

